Much to Experience in Lower Manhattan
May 2023 • Couples
There is much to experience in Lower Manhattan. Highlights include the Financial District with Wall St and the New York Stock Exchange, The 9/11 Memorial and Museum, The Oculus, The One World Trade Center Observation Deck, Trinity Church, Battery Park and boat trips to the Statue of Liberty and Ellis Island and a ride on the Staten Island Ferry. Seeing the Lower Manhattan Skyline from a boat or ferry in New York Harbor is stunning.

Heading South
Oct 2023 • Solo
Manhattan is split into a number of different neighbourhoods and there is plenty to explore. I would recommend paying a visit to Lower Manhattan as there is so much to see here.

There is the Financial District including Wall Street which has lots of beautiful architecture. Also the memorial to the 911 attack is close by. There is also Battery Park which will be familiar to fans of the movie Desperately Seeking Susan.

Close by you can get the ferry across to Ellis Island and the Statue of Liberty and the ferry terminal to get across to Staten Island is also here. I would recommend using this to get some great views of Lady Liberty. Make sure you are on the right hand side of the ferry as you head out.

The area is well served by the Subway and there are buses as well. Plenty of places to get things to eat and drink.
Written December 28, 2023
